<div class="tip_number">TIP 196</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            A child with a headach, a stiff and/or painful neck, and fever should always be seen by a doctor immediately to rule out meningitis. Early diagnosis and treatment are critical. Children with meningitis often refuse to eat and want to be left alone.
        </div>

</div>
